body:
Observations (perhaps not important at all)
invalid_call_argument_test is the only test that tries to listen on 
"0.0.0.0" (other tests listen on 127.0.0.1, "localhost" or "::").

```
g_state.server = grpc_server_create(NULL, NULL);
    grpc_server_register_completion_queue(g_state.server, g_state.cq, NULL);
    gpr_join_host_port(&server_hostport, "0.0.0.0", port);
```

It looks like the way we increase the timeout is wrong.

I think the better way would be adding:

```
if (is_client == 0) {
  g_fixture_slowdown_factor = 5;
}
```

in prepare_test() before line 77.

Note the test tries to create a channel to a non-existent host:port for the test cases with is_client == 1. The previous failures I saw all came from test cases where is_client == 0.
